🌐 What is an API and why is it important?
API stands for Application Programming Interface. It functions as middleware that facilitates communication between two software components using a set of protocols and definitions.

Application: Any software with specific functionality.
Interface: The service contract between two apps that makes communication possible via requests and responses.
Documentation: Information on how developers have structured those responses and requests.

APIs are the essential building blocks for developing complex, enterprise-level applications.

